TITLE: Making Tangle Node Binary Executable (Shell)
DESCRIPTION: This command uses `chmod +x` to add execute permissions to the downloaded Tangle node binary file (`tangle-default-linux-amd64`). This step is necessary to allow the operating system to run the binary file as a program.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tangle-network/docs/blob/main/pages/operators/node-basics/node-software.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
```
chmod +x tangle-default-linux-amd64
```

