TITLE: Configuring Background Service in Blueprint Runner
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to integrate a background service into the Blueprint Runner builder pattern. Includes setup of the service, error handling, and shutdown handler configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tangle-network/docs/blob/main/pages/developers/blueprint-runner/background-services.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
pub async fn main() -> Result<(), Error> {
    let config = Arc::new(Config::default());

    let router = Router::new(config.clone());
    let mut router = router
        .with_producer(
            EventProducer::new("test".to_string(), config.clone())
                .await
                .expect("failed to create producer"),
        )
        .with_job_handler(Box::new(JobHandler::new()))
        .with_consumer(
            EventConsumer::new("test".to_string(), config.clone())
                .await
                .expect("failed to create consumer"),
        )
        .with_background_service(Box::new(BackgroundService::new()))
        .with_shutdown_handler(|| async {
            println!("Shutting down background service...");
        });

    router.run().await?;

    Ok(())
}
```

