TITLE: Defining a Background Service for Tangle Network Blueprint
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to define a background service for a Tangle Network Blueprint. This example creates a simple counter service that increments every second.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tangle-network/docs/blob/main/pages/developers/blueprint-runner/building.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
pub struct Counter {
    count: Arc<AtomicU64>,
}

#[async_trait]
impl BackgroundService for Counter {
    async fn run(&self) -> Result<()> {
        loop {
            self.count.fetch_add(1, Ordering::SeqCst);
            tokio::time::sleep(Duration::from_secs(1)).await;
        }
    }
}
```

