TITLE: Implementing Methods for the Aggregator Context in Rust
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of custom functionality for the AggregatorContext including methods to submit tasks to the task registry contract. The method handles creating the transaction call data, submitting it, and returning the result.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tangle-network/docs/blob/main/pages/developers/blueprint-contexts/eigenlayer-context.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
impl AggregatorContext {
    pub async fn submit_task_to_task_registry(
        &self,
        task_response_commitment: [u8; 32],
        task_response_signature: Vec<u8>,
        task_index: U256,
    ) -> Result<TxHash> {
        let contract = task_registry::TaskRegistry::new(
            self.config.task_registry_addr.parse::<Address>()?,
            Arc::clone(&self.client),
        );
        let call = contract.submit_task_response(
            task_response_commitment,
            task_response_signature,
            task_index,
        );
        Ok(self.submit_transaction(call, "submit_task_response").await?)
    }
}
```

